@satok16 thanks. I see how you did it at the [hexagon_test.cc](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/core/kernels/hexagon/hexagon_graph_execution_test.cc). So how about `.jpg` and `.dat`?  There is a keyboard_299x299.jpg in the test folder, doesn't it have to work out-of-the-box?

hmm, is that the reason there is a python script at `scripts/imagedump.py`. Does it get a .bmp and outputs just the .dat for that matter? Actually, I just used the script to convert the `jpg` to `.dat` and it seems that I passed the image match issue. Now, I am stuck at the error: `execute got err: -1`here:
